This paper discusses the creation of syntactic resources through human editing of tagger and parser output, which falls under the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The study also involves cognitive biases in human decision making, which could be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The experiments and analysis of inter-annotator agreement could be considered as machine learning (cs.LG) or cybernetics (cs.CY) topics. Finally, the discussion of the impact on future annotation efforts and parser evaluations could be relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
